        <h1>Welcome to Lead<span>Pulse</span>.</h1>
		<p>LeadPulse is our new lead intelligence product, providing you on-demand access to key sales metrics including qualitative ratings, contact rates, and feedback about your company and sales process &ndash; directly from surveys sent to buyers we matched to you. LeadPulse data is available in your <a href="[@generateExternalUrl '/sng' /]" title="LeadCenter account">LeadCenter account</a> starting July 3, 2012. </p>
       
		</div><!-- end top content -->
        
        <h3 class="understanding">Understanding your LeadPulse report:</h3>
            [#-- content --]
				
                <img src="[@makeAbsoluteUrl '/images/leadGen/leadPulse_screenshot_script.jpg' /]" alt="Understanding your LeadPulse report" title="Understanding your LeadPulse report" />
        
        <div class="learnlingo">
            <h3>Learn the lingo.</h3>
            <p><strong>Contact rate:</strong> the percentage by which buyers we matched to you are reporting being contacted by you. </p> 
            
            <p><strong>Category contact rate:</strong> the percentage by which buyers in your category overall are reporting being contacted. </p> 
            
            <p><strong>Overall star rating:</strong> how a buyer views your company on a scale of one to five stars (with five stars being a great experience).  Only buyers who indicate having 				heard from you can provide a star rating.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Qualitative rating:</strong> areas of strength and areas of improvement across a number of dimensions as reported directly from buyers.  Buyers may select as many strengths or areas for improvement as necessary. Additionally, open responses will be included.
            </p>
        </div>       

		<div class="emailAlerts">
           <h4>LeadPulse email alerts:</h4>
            <p>It's always good to know where you stand. That's why LeadPulse includes real-time email alerts, so you'll know how to best deploy your sales resources.
            You will receive three types of email alerts:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Deal won:</strong> congratulates you on closing a lead and also includes the primary reason for the buyer selecting your company.</li> 
                <li><strong>Deal lost:</strong> lets you know when a lead has chosen to purchase from someone else and their primary reason for doing so.</li>
                <li><strong>In the running:</strong> reminds you that the buyer is still considering your company, updates their buying timeframe and primary criteria for choosing a seller.</li>
            </ul>
		</div>    	
		
   <div class="questions">
		<h3 class="headline1">Questions? We have answers.</h3>
                <p><strong>When does LeadPulse start?</strong><br />
                 Data will be collected starting July 3rd, but it will take time for results to accumulate, so be patient!</p>
                <p><strong>How is LeadPulse data collected?</strong><br />
                 The data is collected via an automated email survey sent to each buyer, two weeks after their request (and, if necessary, a follow-up survey is sent when they purchase). Historical response rates are approximately 20%.</p>
                <p><strong>How is LeadPulse data available to me?</strong><br /> Your LeadPulse data is available to you on-demand via your <a href="[@generateExternalUrl '/sng' /]" title="LeadCenter account" style="color:#FFF">LeadCenter account</a>.</p>
                <p><strong>Can I turn off LeadPulse email alerts?</strong><br />
                Yes, you will be able to unsubscribe from receiving LeadPulse email should you desire.</p>
                <p><strong>Can I access LeadPulse data without logging into LeadCenter?</strong><br />
                Yes, you will receive your LeadPulse data via email on a quarterly basis.  The data will be aggregated for the previous quarter.</p>
                <p><strong>Will buyers see LeadPulse data?</strong><br />
                At this time, LeadPulse data will not be shared with buyers.</p>
                <p><strong>Why can't I see LeadPulse data in my account?</strong><br />
If you are a new BuyerZone seller, it may take some time for data to accumulate. Additionally, if you are part of a dealer network or receive leads as part of a corporate agreement, you may not have LeadPulse data available in your account. Please contact your account manager to access your LeadPulse data.</p>
			
       </div>
        
